@pluskid 

Thanks a lot

Firstly ELU is part of the Leaky activation functions, so you don't have to add it in activation-inl.h see #718 

What `alpha` did you use? You can set it as slope in the Leaky activation function layer. Currently ELU is implemented following eq. 16 & 17 in the paper, but Caffe has a slightly different definition.

Could you replace:

```
/*! \brief Exponential Linear Unit */
struct elu {
  MSHADOW_XINLINE static real_t Map(real_t x, real_t a) {
    return x >= 0.0f ? x : a * (expf(x) - 1.0f);
  }
};

struct elu_grad {
  MSHADOW_XINLINE static real_t Map(real_t x, real_t a) {
    return x >= 0.0f ? 1.0f : a * expf(x);
  }
};
```

with 

```
/*! \brief Exponential Linear Unit */
struct elu {
  MSHADOW_XINLINE static real_t Map(real_t x, real_t a) {
    return x > 0.0f ? x : a * (expf(x) - 1.0f);
  }
};

struct elu_grad {
  MSHADOW_XINLINE static real_t Map(real_t x, real_t a) {
    return x > 0.0f ? 1.0f : a * expf(x);
  }
};
```

in `src/operator/mshadow_op.h` and see if your network still diverges?
